\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Potatoes, Carrots, onions, turnips, that's about all I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did you have tinned or dried vegetables or fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No. Only tinned fruit occasionally. But not tinned vegetables.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did they keep any livestock for the family? Hens or pigs or goats?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 How many times a week did you eat meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Every day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 How many meals a day did you have meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 One.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 You had it at breakfast of course with your bacon and then again for dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 What about tinned meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Occasionally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 You don't remember how often or what type of meat it was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did you ever get some extra meat such as rabbit from poaching?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Do you remember seeing your mother having less food so that the family could have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did your father have more than your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No. About the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Were you ever allowed to talk during meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Could you choose what you wanted to eat from what was cooked or did you have to eat a bit of everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 We had to have a bit of everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 What was your parent's attitude if you left some food uneaten on the plate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Well they never bothered when we wanted any more because my parents were in b
usiness and we never dawdled over a meal. We hadn't time. After we'd had our plateful and the second course everything was finished.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 They weren't annoyed if you left anything on the plate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 If there was something on the table you want
ed, like the salt, could you ask someone to pass it to you or did you have to wait until it was offered to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Oh no. It was passed to us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Could you ask for a second helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Were you expected to hold your knife and fork in a certain way and sit in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Could you bring toys or books to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 When could you leave the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 As soon as we had eaten out dinner, our meal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did all the family sit at the table for the meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did you always have the same places at the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 How was the meal served - who served it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Mother served.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 What order were you served in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No order at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Where did the younger brothers and sisters sit before they could feed themselves
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Just sat anywhere when they came in from school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 And who fed them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 When did they start to join the family meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 As soon as they started school. Aged 5.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Where did your younger brothers and sisters sit before they could feed themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Don't remember that. I can only remember my sister having a special chair. One of those that you lift up and put the leaf over.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Was your mother an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No because she was rather deaf and we had to repeat ourselves, many times.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did she show you affection?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Very little. I think it was because she was deaf she was always afraid of things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 If you had any worries could you share them with her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 What about your father, was he an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did he show affection?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 If you had any worries could you share them with your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 How did your parents expect you to behave towards them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 They we
re strict. We weren't allowed to have a lot of money to spend. We were always early for school. And we were always sent to school clean and tidy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did they have this attitude of 'speak when you're spoken to' and all that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No. Things were very easy in the home, and at the table.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 
Was your mother a very motherly type of person too, even though she was deaf was she motherly? She used to cuddle you and this sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No. Mother boxed our ears occasionally when necessary. Rather bitter. And that made me rather bitter as I grew older.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did your parents bring you up to behave towards your brothers and sisters in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes. Well we weren't allowed to argue and one didn't get any more than the other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did they say you should hit back or not if another child hurt you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 What kind of people do you think your parents hoped you would grow up to be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Honest and God fearing and they were dead against anything evil, such as betting and anything that was evil.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did your parents bring you up to consider certain things were important in life?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes. Never to tell untruths, and never to steal. And to go to Sunday School and to Church, and to join in games if possible.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 What did they think of swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Very much against it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 When grown-ups were talking were you allowed to join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No. Mother boxed our ears if we did things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 If you did something that your parents disapproved of what happened then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Well we got our ears boxed but never a real good hiding.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Who did the punishing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Mother. Always mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 How often did this happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Occasionally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Never father at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Do you remember any particular occasion when you were punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 
Because my mother was deaf she used to take the wrong idea of things and I often got my ears boxed because I just didn't understand what she wanted. And my idea was that she'd got the wrong end of the stick, when I grew older it made me very bitter, there
f
ore as I grew older I didn't get on with my mother. And although my mother and father taught me to do as I were told, and to be honest and God fearing, it made me dead against what my mother used to try and do to me. I put it down to me being the middle c
hild. My brother was older and my sister was younger and she glorified on them and not on me. They doted on the older one and they made a fuss of the baby one. My sister I think was seven years younger than me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 And you felt that this was why you were unlucky and got the most punishment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 
Yes. My mother was very bitter against me and made my life very unhappy. And she used to tell all the customers that came in our shop what a bad 'un I was and she even sent for the Minister and the Deaconesses of t
he Church to tell them what a bad 'un I was and they used to lecture me. And when my mother died, she got run over in an accident, and her will was read, I'd been left nothing in her will, yet she'd left a few hundred pounds. And as I was walking up the s
treet any time people would turn round and look at me because I'd been such a bad 'un to my mother. And it was very painful.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Would you say that you received the ideas you had about how to behave from both your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 One didn't play a more important part than the other in teaching you these things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 When you had a birthday would it be different from any other day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No. We couldn't afford to celebrate birthdays in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did you receive any presents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did you have anything special to eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No guests to visit you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Can you remember anything you did with your mother or father together on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Only that we all stayed in and just spent it quietly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did you have any musical instruments in the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes. We had the piano and we were all put to the piano, but I never did very much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 You didn't like it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did you have anyone in the family who sang?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Well mother was supposed to have been in the church choir before she was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2649195 Married}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 . But after that she didn't go to church very much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did you ever make music together as a family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did your parents play any games with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes on Sunday evenings we'd play such as Ludo and Snakes and Ladders and things like that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did they play any outdoor games with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Were there any books in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No. But the Minister and the Deaconesses used to lend me books, such as 'The Girl of the Limberlost' and things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 What about newspapers? Did you keep newspapers in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 
Yes. My father was a very good newsagent and did quite a good trade as the years went on, and he kept every periodical but he was only allowed to keep Evening Ne
ws's. The Chronicle and the News were different companies. There was great warfare between the two - between the Evening Chronicle and the Evening News. My uncle farther down the road was a Chronicle agent and there used to warfare between the two - my fa
t
her and my uncle, because one was an Evening News agent and one was an Evening Chronicle agent. And you were supposed if you were an Evening News agent, far superior to an Evening Chronicle agent, because they did a lot of betting and horse racing and the
 Evening News didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 The News Chronicle did a lot of horse racing and betting and of course it was considered wrong to do it was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes. And the bosses of the Evening News were perfect gentlemen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 But you didn't feel this about the Chronicle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 What about magazines? Did you keep magazines in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 
Oh yes. "Home Chat" and all those kind of papers. Lots of magazines - "Girls' Friend", "Boys' Friend". Those were magazines that my father used to sell. He did a very busy trade. Opened his shop at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 18}}}six o'clock{\*\xmlclose} in the morning and kept on 'til {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}
{\xmlattrvalue 0}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 8}}}eight o'clock{\*\xmlclose}
 at night, and we closed at dinner time on Sundays. But he took all the Sunday papers and he had newsboys to take them out and sell them and deliver them to the different hou
ses. The newsboys sold them on the street corner and the Evening News was four-half d a dozen to those newsboys and they sold the Evening News for 1/2d, and they got 15 to the dozen so that they made 2d when they sold a dozen Evening News's.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 And this 
was their profit for doing it, so your father wouldn't pay them a wage actually, they'd make their profit on the newspapers. Do you remember your mother or your father reading?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 My father did Sunday trade and we had two men sleep in the house and they had to be up for {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 14}}}two o'clock{\*\xmlclose} on a Sunday morning to take the papers round to the shops in the districts of {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname 
place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Manchester{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 He was a sort of central depot was he?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes. He was an agent. And we had boys that came and sold on their own, taking them round to the houses.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Do you remember your mother or your father reading?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes they used to read quite a lot of the periodicals and the newspapers that come in, in between customers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did they ever read aloud to you or to each other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Do you remember a funeral in the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes. My grandmother, she lived with us, she died with us. She was buried at Southern }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15690973\charrsid16389298 Cemetery}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Can you tell me who attended?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes, we all went to the funeral, and uncles and aunts all came to the funeral.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did you children go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Can you tell me the type of clothes they wore? What type of mourning clothes they were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 All black for twelve months. They wouldn't have a colour on for that twelve months. Black hat and costume, bla
ck shoes and black stockings, and some had black bordered handkerchiefs. The gentlemen were the same, black bordered handkerchiefs, black suit, black tie, black hat. Wouldn't move from it for twelve months.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Were you taken out visiting neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No. Never. My parents hadn't time for that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 What about friends or relations were you ever taken to visit them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes, occasionally. Sunday tea to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Stockport{\*\xmlclose}
 to some relative. Sunday tea to some one up {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Stretford{\*\xmlclose} way and they used to come to our house for Sunday tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Who took you when you went out visiting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 My parents, both of them, and we'd spend the evening playing games such as Ludo and Snakes and Ladders and things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Were you taken shopping at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Very seldom.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 When you were taken, who took you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Our mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Always your mother, never your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did you ever go out just with your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Very, very seldom. Once he was ill and he went to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Blackpool{\*\xmlclose}
 to recuperate and we went to see him for a few days, the children, me and my brother. He went to a boarding house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Do you remember any other outings with your parents on Bank Holidays or occasions like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No not with my parents. But with Sunday Schools.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did you ever go away for a holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes. From school. We went to the country school at }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15690973\charrsid16389298 Moberley}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298  and we went for a fortnight. And it was to learn nature and it was very interesting. And one or two of the teachers would be with us, and the gardener used to take us
 out on long walks, explaining nature to us. We went twice. It was a sort of boarding school that we were taken to and we slept on the premises and it was very nice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did you ever go with your parents for a holiday, though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No, very seldom, because of the business.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 How often did you go for holidays, with the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Twice we went with the school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 How long did you go for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 A fortnight each time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did the family never go away as a family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Could you tell me how you spent Saturdays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 As I grew older, our church, the Albert Hall, {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}
Peter Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, had Saturday night concerts, and it was 2d to go in. And they were crowded and they were very good and very interesting.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 What type of concerts were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Lovely singing, and perhaps there'd be a conjuror, and a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15690973\charrsid16389298 humorist}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298  and all that, and the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15690973\charrsid16389298 organist}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 
 would give an organ recital and all that kind of thing and it was always very, very nice. And us young girls we would sell programmes. And the Boys Brigade would 
help at the doors taking tickets. And there was refreshments down below. And we used to enjoy the refreshments, of course we had to pay for them. 1d cup of tea and 1d bun. It started at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 19}}}seven o'clock{\*\xmlclose} and finished about {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}
{\xmlattrvalue 30}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 9}}}half past nine{\*\xmlclose}. It finished up with animated pictures.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 How about Sundays, what did you do on Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Well I went to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Sunday{\*\xmlclose} 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Afternoon{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}School{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, and Sunday Evening Service. And then as I grew older I had the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15690973\charrsid16389298 privileged}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298  of taking a Sunday Night class just to mind the children while th
eir parents were in the Service. It was in a little room, and of course I could play the piano so I could play for them singing and I used to tell them Bible stories and as time went on I used to let them play Bible stories. The giant would be over there 
y
ou know, and somebody would shoot a little bit at him. Or Samuel in the temple and we'd build chairs for the children to climb over and stop when they got to a table to rest on a high mountain and then come down another lot of chairs into the temple, then
 
they would kneel down and pray. They did the nativity play and all that. They used to be lovely. This was while their parents were in Church. In those days that I'm talking about there was 2,100 in the congregation. It held 2,100 and it was always packed 
f
ull. And it was to allow the children to come that I took this class. There would be at least twenty children, or thirty, all ages. But before that we had the Sunday Night School but that was for the Deansgate children, for the poorer children. And when t
he war broke out they stopped it and they started this little class that I had. And at Christmas we gave the Nativity Play in the lecture hall to, and actors service in the lecture hall, and I made the costumes and I've still got them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 How old would you have been when you were doing this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Oh since I was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2649195 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 .

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 This wasn't before you were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2649195 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 ? Before 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Before I was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2649195 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 
 too. Yes. Before 1918.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did you have special clothes for Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Only as I grew older, I had, yes. But as a child, no, not very often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did you play games on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Only such as Ludo, nothing in the street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did your parents think it wrong to work or play on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Well I don't think they wanted to let us go out roaming about and them having to come out and look for us, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 It wasn't because they thought there was anything wrong with playing out on Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No, I don't think so.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did your parents attend a place of worship or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Oh yes, the Albert Hall. They attended the Albert Hall. They were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2649195 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298  in the Manchester Mission.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 What was the Albert Hall?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 A {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Methodist{\*\xmlclose} 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}Church{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Peters Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 How often did they go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Every Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Both mother and father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes, usually.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 And you attended every Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes. I was there before them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did you go to Sunday School or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Were there any Sunday School outings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 We had lots of rambles and that into {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Cheshire{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose} and Marple and round there you know, but it 
wasn't an actual Sunday School outing. There'd be a ramble on Saturday and anyone was allowed to go, and any age. We used to have some very lovely rambles. We used to say that this Deaconess she had a sense of direction because we never got lost or anythi
ng.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 What other social activities were there organised by the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Oh there was a Boys' Club and a Girls' Club. Embroidery, singing, dancing, knitting, dressmaking.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did you take part in any of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes. I won one or two prizes for d
ressmaking and that. And I've got about twenty prizes for swimming. They had a swimming club, but I was in the Salford Ladies Club officially, but the Albert Hall had a swimming club.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 And how old were you when you were taking part in it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 About fourteen or sixteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 And what happened when you were in the swimming club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 We used to meet at the High Street Baths, up {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}
Oxford Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. And we had a swimming gala, all the different chapels in the district would put to and have a swimming gala.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 You had competitions and prizes did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 For the girls' clubs that we had. Embroidery and needlework, you know, dancing, singing. We had competitions in the Central Hall, 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Oldham Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, and of course the church that had got the most marks got the shield.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did you belong to the choir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No. But my husband did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Do you know if the choir had any activities?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 They had a picnic once a year and a social once a year. That was all. But they could join in any of the other things that was going.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did the church or chapel run any temperance club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No. But they used to beg of you to sign the pledge. You'd sign that you'd refrain from intoxicating }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15690973\charrsid16389298 liquor}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298  and gambling and all that. And after you'd signed it they gave you the card. They we
re asked from the pulpit "If you would like to sign the pledge there's some stewards in the open way of the hall willing to attend to you". But you didn't have to sign, it wasn't compulsory.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 And did this signing the pledge, did this have a club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 
Oh no. There was a Band of Hope. The Church of England had a Band of Hope and occasionally I went there with my little pals. One or two would recite and tell a story and you'd sing, that hymn "Dare to be a Daniel, Dare to stand alone, Dare to have a contr
ite heart..." that was the hymn they used to sing. We used to be pestered to join the tennis club and the swimming club because we used to be told it taught us to give and take, being in sport, I was in the tennis club as well as the swimming club.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did you play on public tennis courts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 
No it was one that the chapel hired for the year. We had to pay but I forget what it was, it wasn't much. We had teas there. There was a tea tent and we had to take our turn in getting the teas ready and that, you 
know. We had a tent on the field itself. It was there permanently, until the war came along and they took the land. The 1918 war.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Was grace said at meals in your family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No. But in my husband's family it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Who said them in his family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 The father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Were you taught to say prayers at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 
Yes. We'd kneel down beside our bed and say our prayers before we got into bed "God bless Mammy, God bless Daddy and make me a good girl, Amen."
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did you ever have family prayers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did your father take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes. Liberalism.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did he talk about it a great deal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No not a great deal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 You don't know what his views were about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 He didn't say why he was a liberal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Well it was more for the working man and the tradesman. They used to reckon the conservatives were the highbrow and the }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15690973\charrsid16389298 rich men}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 . The labour, the trades unions were coming up with a struggle, you know, and then they started so I think they've almost swamped
 the liberals now. But my father always voted liberal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 And you think this is why he held his views about the liberals, because they were for the working man?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 What about your mother, did she take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 She was liberal too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Do you know what her views were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 
Only that the lot of the working man should be better, and the tradesman should be better, because it was a hard struggle in those days to run a business. We had it very bad and the Albert Hall helped
 my parents very much. They found my father work and once they sent my mother 5/- and we were in the business, then, but things were very bad with us, and we had the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15690973\charrsid16389298 bailiffs}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298  sat in for a week in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Liverpool Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Why did they have the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15690973\charrsid16389298 bailiffs}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298  in, because the business was down?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes and my father had got a loan off a money-lender and he wasn't paying it back and they put the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15690973\charrsid16389298 bailiffs}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298  in. And then one of the shopkeepers signed that if my father didn't pay he'd pay and that then got the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15690973\charrsid16389298 bailiffs}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298  out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 But what happened when the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15690973\charrsid16389298 bailiffs}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298  came?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 
They came into the shop and they showed my mother a paper, and my mother read it and she didn't seem to understand it, I was there at the time, and the man said "Hadn't we better come in and take posses
sion." And they come in, they walked in and they sat in the kitchen all day, and each night they went home and took the key with them, so that they could get in the next day if we turned awkward. And yet, you know, when my father died he left quite a lot 
of money.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 And this was when the Albert Hall stepped in and helped you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes, just before that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 And you think this is why your mother was keen on the liberals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Do you remember your father voting in a General Election before 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes I remember but I don't know who he voted for, I should say it would be liberals.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Can you remember your mother voting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 And do you think that would be for the liberals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes. I remember the suffragettes kicking up a ro
w at all these meetings. I didn't know any personally because I was only a little girl in those days but Christabel and Sylvia Pankhurst used to come and Mrs. Pankhurst.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did they come to your liberal meetings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No. And the Albert Hall invited one
 of them, I don't remember who it was to come and talk to us as they said we should give the suffragettes a fair deal. Votes for women. That's before women had the vote.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Was the minister for it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes, he was for it. He said they should have a say
 in the matter. So that in the girls' club room, it was full of girls, and one of the suffragettes came and told us all about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 How did you feel, as young girls, about the suffragettes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Well we laughed at it you know, it tickled us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Didn't you want to have equal opportunities?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Well it didn't dawn on us in that way, you see. 'Cos that's how they tried to put it across to us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 You didn't feel that there was any injustice in the world when you was young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Not in those days, no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 You were quite content to get }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2649195 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298  and let the man be the boss were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did your mother feel this way too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes - most of the women did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 They didn't agree with this sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No, they used to make fun of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Now how about your father, how did he feel about the suffragettes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 
Well he was the same, all the men were, they were all against it, you know. Oh yes, every man you came across was against votes for women. "What do they want votes for, their p
lace is in the home." And Christabel and her mother used to come, and Sylvia Pankhurst, they were both put in prison I think for it. They spoke in the streets, but we had one suffragette to some and lecture to us in the Albert Hall. The minister said they
 should be allowed to speak and air their views, but he didn't say whether he agreed with them or not.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 
In some places at that time men felt they risked losing their job or their house if they voted differently from their employers. Do you know if your 
father felt himself under that kind of pressure to vote for a particular party? He was in a business of course, though.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 He just voted for who he liked and of course a lot of the men who were under any pressure used to vote secretly and not let on. It
 was a secret ballot and when you'd signed your card you put it in the ballot box.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Do you remember anything about the pressures? How they came about or what happened?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No. Only that's how the C.W.S. come to start under the auspices of the labour party.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 And you feel that this pressure applied to people who worked for the co-operative party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 
Yes. I think they had something to do with the labour movement, you know, the co-operative in those days was very strong and the divi was good. And I
 used to hear talk like this, that if there was a woman in the street not in the co-op, women would stand talking at the entry waiting for this woman coming out to get hold of her and make her join the co-op, by bullying her. They wanted it to get as stro
ng as ever it could get you see. The co-op. They thought it was a good thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did you ever know anyone to whom this happened?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No, only I used to hear people talking in our shop.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Was your father a member of a political party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No. He was never a member.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 So he didn't ever work for any of the parties at an election?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 What about your mother, was she a member of a political party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did your parents take part in any political activity other than at election time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No. In a business you haven't time for much you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 How about the attitude of the people who shopped with you, would your father have to be careful about his politics with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes, he was careful.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 You felt there was a lot of prejudice about whatever party you belonged to in those days? Prejudice between conservatives and liberals?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes, and the conservatives were supposed to be the highest gentlemen in the land.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 So if you lived in a working class district and you sold
 to working class customers, what would you feel the majority of people, what political party would they belong to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 They'd be towards the labour. The working class district. Although we never discussed it in the shop, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Do you remember a great deal about the elections in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No. Only the excitement and {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Albert Square{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose} used to be full waiting for the results coming through and sometimes the Daily Mail in Deansgate had a screen that they used to throw the results on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did you wear rosettes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Well they did, we didn't our parents wouldn't let us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 What about your school friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Oh yes they wore rosettes. I remember Mr. Churchill coming, and my father taking me, he put up as a liberal then, and taking me to the d
ay school that I went to, to one of his meetings. And Churchill's mother was with him and every time he made a statement he turned to his mother for her approval. He wasn't }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2649195 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298  then. His mother used to go with him on all his do's.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did you hear Churchill speak yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes. I was taken by my father. He had a bit of a stammer. He wasn't a good speaker but he had a brilliant mind.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 When your parents were not doing their work, how did they spend their time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Well my father was always busy in the shop.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Didn't he have any leisure at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Well he opened his shop at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 18}}}six o'clock{\*\xmlclose} in the morning, and he went to bed for two hours in the afternoon, because in those days they didn't close the shop 'til {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 10}}}ten o'clock{\*\xmlclose} at night. And when shops had to close at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname 
Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 8}}}eight o'clock{\*\xmlclose} in the evening it was lovely for the shopkeepers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 He never had any leisure at all then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No. In those days, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 What about your mother did she have any leisure or did she work 'til ten at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes sh
e helped my father in the shop, and did her housework. She had one or two women occasionally but only for a week or two, to clean, but they were very unreliable.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 What did they do when they cleaned?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 They cleaned the bedrooms and that, you know. S
o that in the end I had to clean my own bedroom and sometimes clean my mother's bedroom. But in those days you used to get on your hands and knees and wash the floor. That was it in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 So your mother wouldn't have a great deal of time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did your mother have any interests outside the house at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 
She'd go to the chapel. And then we had bills for the theatres and we used to get passes for the theatre. Her and my father would go to the theatre. A pass was a free ticket for two in the circle.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did your mother go out to enjoy herself at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No. Very little. Only to the theatre with my father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 She always went with your father if ever she went out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Your father worked on the premises of your shop didn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 So he'd no }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15690973\charrsid16389298 travelling}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298  at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did your father attend any clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did he go to the pub at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Was he teetotal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes. Well he drank in his early days but he got eczema very bad and th
e doctor told him he'd have to come off the chemics. So he never drank any more.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did your mother go out to any clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did she ever go to the pub?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No. My mother never went in the pubs with my father because women weren't allowed in
 the vault. It was very bad to see a woman in the vault, but they were allowed in the best rooms, and the best rooms are always a bit on the dearer side. They charged more for having anything in the best room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did your father take part in any sport?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did he attend the races?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did he ever bet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 
No. And we used to sell loads of tips. Different men used to bring envelopes and say "I've got the winner in this envelope." They were tipsters, they called them. Any man could do
 it. They'd bring you a dozen envelopes "Will you sell these for me?" Perhaps sell them for 6d, they perhaps would charge us 3d.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 So any man in the local street could be a tipster?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did you know anyone who made a living at this?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 W
ell not personally. I knew the men that used to come in my father's shop, they used to go round to all the shops and sell these tips in envelopes. The tip was what was supposed to be the winner of certain races and it was type-written on a piece of paper 
inside the envelope.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Well what would happen would they go and buy a typewriter to do this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 I suppose so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Even poor men?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 They weren't really poor men. You could say business men, they were. Just like my father would be, a business man y
ou see. Some had a rubber stamp and put the letters in, and stamped it on the paper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 But how do you think they got the tips?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Oh they only guessed them, by studying form and all that, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 What did your father feel about betting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Oh very bitter my father was, because such a lot of poor people did the betting. And the bookies were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15690973\charrsid16389298 Catholics}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298  and they made such a splash on Friday when they were walking.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Were they all }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15690973\charrsid16389298 Catholics}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 , do you think, the bookies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Oh no, but the bookie near us was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did your father or mother belong to any savings clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No. They were in the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Manchester{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 and Salford Bank all their lives.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 They weren't in a boot club or a sick club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Or a funeral club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No. Oh perhaps a funeral club, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 This came under the insurance did it, as insurance, it wasn't a funeral club run locally by any one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Oh no. Like the Refuge Assurance Company and all that, you know. 2d or 3d a week it used to be.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 How did you get on with your brothers and sisters.?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 
Well not too well because my mother used to tell them what a naughty girl I was. So they didn't treat me very nice. They didn't speak nicely to me. But I think it was because I was the middle one.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 So you didn't get on with them very well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Do you think they didn't like you as a person or do you think it was just your mother's influence?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Just my mother's influence.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 How did you feel about them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Oh I took no notice. I don't believe in retaliating.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Was there anyone you felt particularly close to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 
Only my Grandmas - My Grandma Spong and Grandma Turner. I felt very close to them because they always spoke kindly to me, you see. And the Deaconesses at the Albert Hall they were very decent, even though my mother used to go and tell them tales about me.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 As a child who did you play with? Did you play with your brother and sister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No. I played with other girls that went to school with me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Where did you play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 In the streets, we played in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Not in a garden or a yard?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No. We'd no gardens
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did you ever play in anyone's home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes occasionally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Anywhere else you played?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Nowhere else. We went to the Band of Hope and things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 What about parks?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 What games did you play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 
We used to play rounders in the streets. And ball, and skipping rope, Milligators, we used to call it. You had a rope right across from one set of footpath to the other and there'd perhaps b
e twenty of you and you'd go through this rope, and the next time you'd jump twice and out, and the next time you'd jump three times and out, while they were turning the rope. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15690973\charrsid16389298 
And the one that was faulty in the rope, she had to take the end and do the turning up and let that one come into the rope. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 
And we used to play hide and seek. And the boys played coppers and thieves - the thieves had to hide and the coppers had to find them, and then they changed places with the police.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Were you allowed to get dirty when you played?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 
No we never got very dirty. But our headmistress used to cane us if we went with dirty hands, so that made us keep clean. We always had a wash before we went to school again after dinner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Your parents never worried if you got your clothes dirty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Were you free to play with anyone you pleased?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did your parents discourage you from playing with certain children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did you belong to any youth organisation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No. There wasn't any in those days. There was the Band of Hope and the Church Club, but it was never called a youth organisation.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 And what did you do at these clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 We did embroidery and millinery and different things. And the boys they did gymnastics and al
l that, you know. Then I went to night school quite a lot, to Manchester Central Schools, in the evening and took millinery, dressmaking, cooking and tailoring.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 How did you spend your free time when you were at school? Did you have any hobbies then? D
id you keep pets or do gardening or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 
No there was no gardens in Deansgate. No we used to go out to these different clubs we had and played in the streets in the summer days, but not in the winter time. Course we had to go to bed about seven or {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 8}}}eight o'clock{\*\xmlclose}, however old we were we weren't allowed to be up very late.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 You didn't go fishing, walking or bicycling?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 We did have bicycles and we went journeys, as we grew older though, that was. We never went fishing. We went ramb
ling quite a lot with the Albert Hall, but never with our parents. We went away on week's holidays with the Albert Hall to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}Wales{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 and different places.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Was this while you were at school you went with the Albert Hall as well as with the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 And how long did you go for when you went with the Albert Hall?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 About a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 
I know once we went to Matlock, I've got a photograph of us all; there was about a dozen girls and I think it was 5/- for the week, for the food and everythi
ng. Some of the ladies, what they called the Honorary Sisterhood, they used to send us on these holiday do's and they'd send a hamper of food so that the Albert Hall hadn't to charge us much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 The Honorary Sisterhood?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Ladies, wives of business me
n, and there were some, believe me, in the Manchester Mission. The committee of the Manchester Mission was all business men and my word they used to see to things. We used to have some very lovely socials.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 And it was run by these women?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes. The
 Girls' Club, the president was a Miss Moon, and she had a brother, Dr. Moon, and she had a brother a solicitor; well she paid for a lot of those things. And we used to have Garden Parties in aid of the Missionaries and rich business men would open their 
gardens to us, outside {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Manchester{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
, Flixton and all round there. On a Saturday afternoon. A Missionary Garden Party, we'd go to. We'd have games and races and afternoon. A Missionary Garden Party, we'd go to. We'd have games and races and afternoon tea on th
e lawn and all that. The games - running, and throwing a ball and skipping and all that, you know. Competitions.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 And the prizes were provided by whom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 The people that owned the house. Business men.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did you do any sport of any kind?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Ye
s I was a swimmer and I was in the Albert Hall hockey team. And I were in their Rambling Club. And I have about twenty prizes for swimming.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 These were pre-1918, were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Oh yes, when I was a youngster. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15690973\charrsid16389298 
I won a tea-service, that was in Broughton Swimming Club, I won that. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 
And a pair of silver vases, and a clock and three medals, and two certificates. A little fancy clock that would go on the sitting room mantelpiece, not a great heavy thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did you go to any theatres?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes. We used to
 go to the Manchester Palace, the Tivoli that was opposite the Albert Hall - that was a very nice place, because we used to have bills up for them and we used to get two passes, I think it was once a month.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 What about concerts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Oh yes. I went to the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Halle{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 a few times and the Albert Hall had concerts.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 You went as a child to the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Halle{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 
Well not quite as a child, when I was about sixteen, or seventeen. And then the Albert Hall had Saturday night concerts, they were very nice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 What type of concerts were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 
Madam Bella Bailey and Madam Louise Fidler they were favourite singers. It was singing. It was nothing of low class, you know, and it ended up with pictures.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did they give their services voluntary?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No they got paid. I believe 1 g}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15690973\charrsid16389298 uinea}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298  an evening, they got for singing. There was always a ventriloquist and always a humorist. Somebody to make us laugh, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did you go to cinemas while you were still at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes once or twice. We had bills up for the cinemas and we used to get tickets for them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did your parents give you any pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 
Yes. About 2d or 3d a week as we grew older. On a Saturday when we were young we got a Saturday 1/2d. And with a sister of my father's farther down {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Liverpool Road
{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, she gave us a Saturday 1/2d. And I think altogether we got four Saturday 1/2d. And we went to Marks and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15152215\charrsid16389298 Spencers'}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298  to spend it. To their penny bazaar.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Do you remember the things you bought with it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No I don't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Marks and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15690973\charrsid16389298 Spencers'}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298  would be very small then wouldn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No. Like what the bazaars are now. You've seen their bazaars, but they were only 1d in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did anyone outside the home help your mother look after her house or family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No relations or friends or neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 If your mother was ill or confined to bed, how did she manage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 
Well the only time she was ill and confined to bed was over a confinement. I think she reckoned she'd had eight children but only three survived. And 
the midwife, the woman that nursed her, came in to do for us. There wasn't a qualified midwife in those days.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Do you remember what happened when your younger sister was born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 My mother had an unqualified woman to look after her. I can't remember whether she had the doctor. I don't think she did. A
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did you have any relatives living nearby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did you see them very often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes, but they were in the newspaper shop lower down the road and my parents and them weren't on speakin
g terms but we used to go in every Saturday and ask for our Saturday 1/2d.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did your parents have friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Where did they see them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Well in our houses, but they didn't visit friends very much. They just had friends come occasionally on Sunday evenings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did they share the same friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did your mother have friends of her own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 What about your father, did he have friends of his own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No. You see they met at the Methodist Chapel so the friends at the Methodist Chapel were friends of both my parents.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Were friends ever invited into the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Not a lot of friends. Only very intimate friends. Very old friends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 How often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 About once a month.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Would they be offered anything to eat or drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes, they'd have Sunday afternoon tea together or even supper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Was it on any particular days or occasions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Sundays only.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Would you say that the friends invited in were your mother's friends or your father's friends, or friends of both of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Friends of both of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did friends call in casually without an invitation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No. Usually had an invitation.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 What about neighbours, did they call in casually?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Well we didn't have a lot of neighbours in. My mother didn't believe in neighbouring.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did your parents ever go out to visit friends or neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 
Relatives we used to go to. One lived at Stockport, they used to go and see them. And one up the Chester Road, Hulme, used to go and see them. But that was about all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 
People often tell us that in those days they made their own amusements. What do you think your parents did when they got together with their friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 They just sat and talked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 They didn't play any music?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 They didn't make their own amusements?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Never played games?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 
Many people divide society into different social classes or groups. In that time, before 1918, did you think of some people belonging to one class and some to another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Could you tell me what the different ones were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 The }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15690973\charrsid16389298 lower middle}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298  classes were shopkeepers and small business people. The higher were landed gantry, dukes and earls. The middle class were professional men, doctors, lawyers, dentists, business executives, teachers. Artisans, skilled }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15690973\charrsid16389298 craftsmen}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 , having served 5 or 7 years apprenticeship. And the labourers were building, building and cleansing.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Which class would you say you belonged to yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 The middle class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 What sort of people belonged to the same class as yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 The middle class - shopkeepers, tradesmen, nurses.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Will you tell me again what sort of people you thought belonged to the upper class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Landed gentry, dukes and earls, professional men, doctors, lawyers, dentists, business executives.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Do you feel that they belonged to the upper class, the doctors and the business executives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Well the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15690973\charrsid16389298 lower middle}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298  classes were shopkeepers and small business men and the lower classes were artisans and labourers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 
Can you remember being brought up to treat people of one sort differently from people of another? Were you ever told to curtsey; touch your cap; or show respect in some way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No. We were never taught that because that was just before our time, curtseying to people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 But were you brought up to treat people of one sort differently, to show respect to certain people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Oh yes. We had to speak very politely to them and not be rude in any way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Which people would this apply to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Well doctors and lawyers, and the landed gentry, dukes and earls.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Well what about the people you lived with? How did you have to treat them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Well those that were customers of my parents we had to treat them as nice as we could.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Was there anyone you called 'sir'?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 
No. We never knew anybody to call them 'Sir'. Well, a foreman in a factory or the owner of a factory, we might call 'sir', but we never met a man who had the title of 'Sir'.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 What about 'master'?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 What about 'madam'?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Well it was "Yes, miss; no, miss." To a foremistress in a works, not 'madam'. Madam's a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2649195 
Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298  lady and it's very seldom there was a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2649195 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 
 lady foremistress in a works.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Do you remember anyone showing respect to your parents in these ways?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Oh yes. Customer's were always very respectable to my parents because they were always very respectable to them. To customers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 In the district where you lived, who were considered the most important people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 The doctors and the owner of the chemist's shop, and the owner of the big grocer's shop, and the owner of a big drapery shop.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did you ever come into contact with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes because we bought from these shops.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Why did you consider them important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Wel
l we considered them important because we supposed they were a bit better off than a little shopkeeper and they had big shops and we had to call them 'sir'.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Now what about shopkeepers who did they associate with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Well shopkeepers didn't get very
 far because they'd always such a lot of work to do after they'd closed, and they never seemed to associate with one another. They didn't on the row of shops that I lived in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 What about the clergymen, who did they associate with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Well we never s
aw them associating with anybody only the very high members of the church. Like the Sunday School Teachers and the Superintendent of the Sunday School.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 What about teachers, who do you think they associated with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Well they lived such a long way o
ff the teachers did from the slums where we lived that we never saw anything more of them after school hours.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 What about farmers, did you ever know any farmers in that district?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Not in the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15690973\charrsid16389298 Deansgate}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298  district. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 What about employers, who do you think they associated with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 
Well they seemed to live right on the outskirts of Manchester, therefore those people who lived on the outskirts of Manchester would associate with one another wouldn't they. Say in the Freemasons and those kind of things.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 What sort of people would you say went to Church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Some very poor and some quite rich. And the very poor went to see what they could get.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 How do you mean, what they could get?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Well the parson to ask them "How's things Mrs. So a
nd So? I'll come and see you then." And try to put things right for them. That type of thing you see. Sometimes they'd get a grant from the poor box of the Church to help to pay the rent or something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 What sort of people do you think went to Chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 
Well the lower classes went to Chapel. And the Free Churches did a lot for poor people in those days. They did for my parents. They found my father work to get my parents on their feet again in the business and they looked after my mother. They came t
o see her once or twice. They gave her 5/- one time. And when my father got sacked from where they got him work they got him work again. And it put our business on its feet doing that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Do you remember any prejudice against the Roman Catholics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Oh yes, there was a lot, where we lived.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Can you tell me anything about it. What forms did it take?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 
Well they wouldn't mix with each other, you know, and they were jealous of the performance they put out on a Whit Friday when they were walking. 'Cos they always put a lovely procession on, the Roman Catholics, much nicer one than the Protestants.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 And you felt that the Protestants were jealous of the Roman Catholics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes. And yet I have great respect for the Roman Catholics myself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 But in those days you remember prejudice against them and this was the main form.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 It's nothing to do with the religion at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No. You see if you was a catholic you could get a job if the boss was a catholic and all that, whereas a Chu
rch of England man or a Methodist man wouldn't bother what denomination you belonged to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 So there was also prejudice on the Catholic side as well as the Protestant side?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Where you lived, did all the people in the working class have the same standard of living, or would you say there were different groups?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 
Oh there was different groups because there was men's lodging houses and women's lodging houses and there was a lot in the Deansgate area.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Can you tell me anything about the lodging houses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 
I used to go with the Albert Hall to hold meetings in those places, and the men carried a little harmonium and I played it for them. In these lodging houses.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 And how old would you have been then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 About sixteen or seventeen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Can you tell me more about them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 
Well the floors had always got sand on them, there was no lino or carpet laid. And they had to do their own cooking and get their own meals ready on a stove and all that, you know. There was never meals prepar
ed for them. And there was a man in charge and if anything went wrong he'd throw the people out that were causing the trouble. And it was said that these people that lived in these lodging houses, this was in the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15690973\charrsid16389298 Deansgate}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298  district, they had to sleep with the money under the mattress otherwise it would be stolen during the night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Was this just men's lodging houses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Men's and women's lodging houses.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 The same things applied to the women's did it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes. A respectable woman didn't stay in t
hose women's lodging houses any longer than she could help. If she could get a job of service living in, she'd jump at it. And it was only the lower class women that sort of lived on prostitution and that lived in those lodging houses.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Now then what a
bout the different classes of working class people, did you find they were different classes and what was the difference between them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Well a typist, if a girl was a typist they thought she was very well up, especially if she could do shorthand. And 
of course there was some families around the Deansgate area that sent their children to Duty Avenue School where you had to pay a fee, my sister went to that. You had to pay to go there so if you went to that school you were certainly somebody in the Dean
sgate area.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 What about the difference in families? What about a labourer's family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 
A labourer's family lived in little houses, two up and two down, no bath, no wash-house, very little yard and most of the women had to go to the local wash-house that was just about opening in my younger days.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 What about the slightly better class amongst the working class then, not the labourers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Well the better class usually had their own boiler in their house so that they could do their washing inside 
the house. My mother had a boiler. It was a square brick affair with a little fire underneath and on top you lifted a lid and there was a big metal bowl. And you put your water in there and lit the fire underneath, boiled the water, and you washed your cl
othes in that. And filled the boiler up again and let the whites boil in the boiler to keep them a good colour.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Do you think that one group felt itself superior to the rest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes. Shopkeepers and those that had good jobs in town, clerks, and diffe
rent people, felt far superior to a labourer or anybody that had been in prison or that kind of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Were some families thought of as rough and others as respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Definitely. The rough ones certainly lived rough, sort of the kitchen where 
they lived they had no lino on, they would white-stone it instead of having lino on, whereas the better ones had lino on the kitchen floor. But none had carpets in the bedrooms they used to say that it caused bugs and fleas. They just had lino on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Do you remember a distinction of this kind between craftsmen and labourers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 
Oh yes. Yes. Like all the shopkeepers would have better homes than the people who lived at the back of us in a little street called White Lion Street. The craftsmen lived in bet
ter streets, wider streets, not little narrow streets in the Hulme district you'd find the better class craftsmen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Lid your mother and father have the same attitude to people in different classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes because my father went to a paid school and with my mother marrying him it lifted her up a bit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 And they both felt the same about different classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Do you think your mother saw herself as belonging to a particular social class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No. Not to a particular social class, but sh
e classed herself as a bit higher than the women that lived in women's lodging houses. She'd ambitions for us to be better educated.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Do you think it was possible at that time to move from one class to another?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No. Only by getting certificates to say that you could do certain jobs and then you would be in a bit higher class, than the labourer.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Can you remember anyone who did this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Well my brother, he went to night school for electrical work and the night school took him on as a teacher
, without having his teacher's certificate because he'd done so well at night school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Do you remember anyone being described as a 'real gentleman' or a 'real lady'?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Well yes I do. One or two that were clerks in charge of the railway and things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Why do you think they were referred to as a 'real gentleman' or a 'real lady'?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 
Well they must have been greatly respected by the men that worked under them otherwise we shouldn't have thought that. We wouldn't have heard anything about them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 It was usually the men who worked under them who referred to them like this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Do you remember seeing a policeman around where you lived as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Oh yes, we had plenty of policemen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 What did you think of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Oh we used to like policeman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did your mother ever say, when you'd done something wrong, 'I'll call a policeman'.?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes. But we were always taught that if we were in any trouble to go to a policeman and not to a stranger.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 How do you think he treated the people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 He treated them very well as long as they treated him very well. He interfered with nobody.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Was your home rented, your shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes. Rented.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did you ever see anything of your landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 The collector to Wilson's Brewery.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 The house belonged to Wilson's Brewery?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes. The pub was next door to our shop.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 So had you any feelings about your landlord? What did you feel about him as a landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Always all right. No trouble.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Do you remember feeling that your parents had to struggle to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes. They had a terrific struggle.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 What did you feel about it? What did you think about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Well it used to worry me as a child so I was glad to get to work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 What difference did it make to the family when your father was ill or out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Well to tell you the truth we had the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15690973\charrsid16389298 bailiffs}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298  at him for a few days, through me father having to get a loan through a money lender.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 How often was your father out of work or ill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 
Well he wasn't supposed to be in work but he went to work because things was so bad in the shop. When the shop bucked up, when more people got in the district and things were busier he gave his work up and looked after the shop.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 What did he do when he was actually out of work, as well as running the shop, what were the jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Oh no jobs when he was out of work he just helped in the shop serving.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 But during the time that he did go out to work to help out the shop, what type of job did he do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 He worked at Brookes and Docks in Hardwick, an Engineers, and he worked at the Western House. They were like labourer's jobs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 But he wasn't ill very often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did you ever get any help from the Guardians or the parish?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No but the Manchester Mission sent us some money once and got my father work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 How did they treat you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Very nicely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 How did you feel about having to take help from them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 We felt very grateful.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Were you given lessons by one of your parents, or a tutor, or a governess?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Well I had music lessons but nothing to help me at school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 How old were you when you first went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 When you first started what time of the morning did you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Nine o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 And what time did you come back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Half past four.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 What age were you when you started afternoon school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 It was a full day school right from the age of five. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 What kind of school was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Well it was a very nice school. It was cal
led St. Matthews Infants School. And the headmistress was a very nice elderly lady, and the teachers were young ladies but in those days they weren't qualified, but they were very nice, young ladies come from good homes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Was it a girls' or mixed school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Mixed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Was it a day school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Was it a church school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Church of England?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 How did you get to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Well it was only a minute's walk. It was in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}
Liverpool Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} where I lived.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Who went with you to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 I went on me own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 From five?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Where did you have your {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 12}}}midday{\*\xmlclose} meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 
At home. Although they had a soup kitchen for children. The caretaker used to make soup every day in his big boiler in the cellar, and we could buy pennyworths and halfpennyworths of soup, and we did occasionally and take it home with us for our dinner.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Was this soup always sold, or did any children have it free?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No it was always sold. Well I think it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 And the caretaker always made it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Always made it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 You don't know where he got the materials; it was supplied by the Education committee?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No. He just made it himself. He was a good }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15690973\charrsid16389298 Christian}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298  man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 What did you think of school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Oh I liked school very much. I was sorry to have to leave. I only wished I could have gone to a {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Higher{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}School{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 How did you feel about the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 I used to like me teachers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did the teachers emphasise certain things as important in life, like manners or tidiness?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 
Yes. Manners and tidiness and to keep your fingers clean, and keep your finger nails clean. And to look after your hair because there was lice in those days in anybody's hair. And to keep your body clean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 What did they tell you about manners?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 
Well they didn't tell us a lot about manners but they set us an example in their manners. By saying thank you if we did anything for them and all that kind of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 What about punctuality?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Well they were keen on that. But if you were la
te a lot of times you would perhaps get the cane. But sometimes it was through the mother being a bit dilatory about it. But I was never late.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did they impress you about ways of speaking at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes they used to pull us up about speaking nicely.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 If you did something the teachers disapproved of what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Well we'd perhaps get the cane. Just a little tap you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did they give it to girls as well as boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 What were the things they gave you the cane for? What were the offences?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 
Well such as having dirty hands when we'd been told to wash our hands before we come to school that day. Or being late too often. Or not paying attention, talking while teacher was talking. Things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did your parents show an interest in your school work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did they ask you what you did at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did they visit the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No. They was never invited. Parents weren't invited.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did they meet the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did the other children come from similar types of home to your own or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes. Even poorer homes than mine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did the teachers single out some children for different treatment from the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No. But the cleaner children and those that were early at school were made the monitors to help the teachers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Were there any gangs or groups in the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Were there any children who were left out of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Well perhaps there were a few because their parents didn't take an interest i
n the happenings at school and other things you know. But it would only be a few.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 How many schools did you go to? Did you go on to another school after this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes to the Big School. Just across the road from the Infants School that we'd been to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 What age would you have been when you went there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 About seven or eight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 And was this boys, girls or mixed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 All girls.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 And you were still only a minute away from school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 When you got to this big school did you stay for dinner or did you come home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 I came home for dinner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 What did you think of this school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 
Very nice. Good school. Very nice young ladies but they were all unqualified it only came in a few years after that that every teacher had to be qualified. But for music and things like that they were excellent.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 And did the teachers in this school emphasise certain things as important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Oh yes. Cleanliness, we often had to show our hands and finger nails.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 And were they keen on manners and punctuality?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 And ways of speaking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Now what happened in this school if you did something the teachers disapproved of?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Well we'd get the cane. But the headmistress always gave it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 What offences did you get it for in this school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 
Well speaking when we shouldn't be talking or pushing somebody down the steps or some children would swear because they'd heard their parents swear.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did your parents show an interest in what you did at this school? Did they ask you what you did at this school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did they visit the school at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No. There was no need, they lived too near, they could almost know what was going on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 And did the children here come from similar types of home to your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did the teachers here single out some children for different treatment from others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15690973\charrsid16389298 Well not single treatment. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 
If they were naughty they'd have to go to the headmistress and get the cane. But if you were good you were sent to 
swimming lessons and cookery lessons to other schools that had a cookery room and things like that, if you were naughty you weren't allowed to go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 What about gangs or groups?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No there was no gangs or groups.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Any children who were left out of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 How old were you when you left school finally?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Fourteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Would you have stayed longer if you had had the opportunity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes I would have loved to have stayed longer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did you go to any part-time education afterwards? Evening classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 
Yes I went to Manchester Central Schools but you couldn't start there I don't think 'til you was sixteen. I went for tailoring and cookery and embroidery. Different nights of the week and I used to go straight from work, and I enjoyed every minute of it.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Do you have any regrets about your education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No. I only wish I could have had a better one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Do you think you benefited from attending school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Oh yes. I've got some very nice embroidery of my own that I did 
at the night school, and I used to make my own hats at millinery lessons, and tailoring lessons and then I went to work in a tailor's shop and earned very good money.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 So it was worthwhile?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 While you were at school did you have a pa
rt-time job or any means of earning a little regular money? This was while you were young and at school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Now I should like to ask you about your first full time job. What was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Well my really first full time job was in a tailor's f
actory. That I felt I'd got a good job. Before that I was an errand girl for an embroidery firm and different things. I had quite a few little tiny jobs that weren't satisfactory.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 What type of jobs were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Well one was on office, they'd two o
r three rooms, and they sold everything for embroidery, to shops, and they'd two or three travellers, and I was the errand girl for that place.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 This was your first full time job was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 And what did you do after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 The after t
hat I worked at a jewellers, a manufacturing jewellers, but that wasn't nice. Everything after it was cleaned was cleaned in, what do they call it that red stuff, and we'd to wash all that red stuff out. And we didn't like that at all because we worked in
 a very dark cellar. Oh the red stuff was rouge.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did you do another job before you eventually went to tailoring?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 The tailoring was four jobs. One was the job, children's underwear, that you had to work three months for nothing. And then the rouge
 business. And then the embroidery place. And then I went to Cohen and Wilkes the tailors and that's where I stayed, until I had to leave.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 How did you get the job? Did you get it through your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No. They were advertising for girls to learn
 the trade. First they put me on what we call cleaning, on the cleaning table. Perhaps a dozen girls round a big table and they were cutting all the ends off wherever they could find an end on a tailored garment. Ends of cotton, and trimming things up, an
d
 all that. And then they put me on finishing. I asked to go on finishing, I asked to go on my own time. That was sewing the linings in and sewing the buttons on and sewing the hangers on and all the little bits that the machinist couldn't get to. Sewing t
hem by hand. And I earned very good money on that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did you get your money from the beginning of the job or did you have to serve an apprenticeship?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No. I hadn't to serve an apprenticeship with it. They put a girl to show me how to do it for abou
t a week and then I used to earn three or four pounds a week in those days. That was very good money in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 What hours did you work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Eight o'clock 'til six o'clock. And we were able to buy a cooked dinner. Dinners were 2d, and very good 
dinners they were. The owner used to say that if he fed his girls well they would work well. And they also had me on the girls' committee.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 What were the years you were at this firm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Well I was there when the armistice came. I was there about fou
r years, from 1916.-1919. And when the armistice came a buzzer blew and we all went out of the shop.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Tell me about the girls' committee?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Well I was on the girls' committee and the owner, Mr. Cohen, took the chair always. And we discussed any lit
tle difficulty that was happening in the works as regards the welfare of the girls. And there was 2000 girls worked in one room. It was a very large room. It was very crowded.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 How did you feel about this? Did you find it oppressive to be in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Oh no. Because it was modern. It had been specially built for this 'ere war work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 So you enjoyed your work did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Oh yes I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did you work Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No. Nor Saturdays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did you have a half-day in the week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Will you tell me more about this girls' committee, what actually happened, what it did, what its functions were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 
Well if there were any grumbles, or if the dinners weren't in order, or there used to be a tea-wagon come round. Or if any girls wasn't playing th
e game on any bench (you mean not doing the work properly? yes) They weren't keeping up with the work or they were doing a lot of grumbling. If there was a lot of grumbling and we let it out at this committee the boss would see that there was no need to g
rumble and all that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Suppose you thought the girls had a real grumble would you take this to the boss on the committee only in the form of a trade union idea?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes. Something like a trade union, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Would he always listen to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Oh yes, and he always had it put right. Always. It was a lovely firm to work for.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 How did you get on to the committee?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 They just come and asked me would I. The manager just come and asked me would I sit on the committee.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 You weren't elected by the other girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did the other girls ever grumble if they didn't get on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did you have holidays with pay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No. No holidays with pay, but I did have holidays. We worked on our own time and it was a very big room and the gar
ments were cut up above and they started at that end of the room and they gradually come along the different benches and when they got to that end of the room they were finished.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 And you each did a section did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes. Section of work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Was it good rate of pay for the job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 
Oh yes. We got 8d for sewing 100 buttons on. And 2 1/2d for sewing a lining in, and we had to fell it in and felling is a certain way of stitching so it can't be drawn out. And doing button holes and sewing the tabs 
on at the back. And we had to finish the buttons off with two stitches on the wrong side. And the passers would hold it up to see that the buttons stood up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 How did you make the buttons stand up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 By shan}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15152215\charrsid16389298 king}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298  it well, with thick heavy thread.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 And what were you paid for these items as you did them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 8d for 100 buttons, and they'd count so many buttons for sewing a hanger on. And we had to bar}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15152215\charrsid16389298  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 tack button-holes. The machine would just do the button-hole and then we had to put a bar}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15152215\charrsid16389298  
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 tack across. And we got 8d a 100 for that. A bar}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15152215\charrsid16389298  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 
tack would be called 2 buttons and a hanger 4 buttons. The buttons had to stand up well and in between the buttons we had to sew the fly, (flange which hid buttons on front of raincoats) and we had to put stitches here and there to stop it flying open.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did you feel it was a fair wage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes, I made }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5310954 \'a3}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 3 or }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5310954 \'a3}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 4 a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did you give any of the money to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes. And then she got so vexed with me, she said I'd got to pay her so much, so I paid
 her a part of my wage, so on my way home from work I used to call at Manchester and Salford Bank and put the rest in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 What was it spent on, the money you gave your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Well it was for keeping me you see. And there used to be some awful rows about what I was earning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 She knew how much you earned did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No but she must have suspected things. But I always gave her what she asked me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 How did you get on with the other people you worked with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Very well. Very, very well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 How did your employer treat you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Very well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 How did you feel about him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 
Oh I loved my employer. There was two or three foremen and I got on very well with them, and then there was a manager and I got on very well with him. And then there
 was the owner, Mr. Cohen, and I got on very well with him. And Mr. Cohen used to give concerts to the wounded soldiers and we used to go and wait on, and he would sing and his wife would play the piano. So they were educated.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 How did you feel about the work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 I liked the work very much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 
Did the job alter your attitude to school? A lot of people when they leave school and go to work they have a totally different attitude to school, did this happen to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 What jobs have you done since the First World War?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 None.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Would you have preferred another type of occupation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No. I would have liked a profession, but when I see some of the professions I think well I'm as well in this. In a shop.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Because you feel it pays better?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did you serve an apprenticeship or training period for any of your jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Not even your tailoring job, did you not consider that a training period?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No because I went to night school for it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did you belong to any trade union?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No. They were trying to get a trade union going in Cohen and Wilks but it wasn't successful.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 You never took part in any of the activities?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did you feel that employers and workers had the same interests or different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 I reckon they had the same interests. The Cohen and Wilks business, because Mr. Cohen was a gentleman in every way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 In what way did they both have the same interest did you feel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 The employer wanted to get the work out for the war, it
 was uniforms, and the workers wanted to earn the money. And he supplied us with dinners and the tea wagon came round so it kept us going beautifully so that we were pleased to work in that way. We were pleased to work for him and he was pleased for us to
 work so hard.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did you feel that there were divisions of interest among workers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 
Well there was among workers because what they called a cleaner, they went over the garment and cut the ends off that we'd left, well they'd no skill about them; we 
had the skill. And then there was the cutting room, they had the skill, and there was one gentleman over the cutting room, you see he was the boss of the cutting room. Then there was the pressers, big, burly women, and they didn't stand on any dignity.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 And you felt this was the difference between you, not the difference in your jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No. The difference in our dignity.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did you feel there was a difference though, between trained craftswomen and the other workers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 You felt there was a great difference did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Would you say that full time work changed your general attitude to life in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Oh yes it did because I felt I was wanted and I was happy and I was earning the money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 How did you feel you were wanted?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 
The work wanted me you see. They welcomed me to go and work for them, they were so short of staff in those days, for turning uniforms out, so that you felt you was wanted. And you was very happy in it. And the tea came round in the middl
e of the morning and there was lovely dinners, but they expected you to work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 So it changed your general attitude?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 And going home on Friday night I used to call at the Manchester and Salford Bank and put some of me money in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 I'd like to ask you about your life at home after you left school? Did you continue to live at home then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did starting full time work change your relationship with your parents at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No. Not much. It was only me mother, me father was
 very kind, but she was never satisfied at the money I brought home you see. So that I asked at work to be put on a better job, and they put me on a better job, and I was able to give me mother what she wanted but I never told her how much I earned.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did it change your relationship in any other way, apart from the money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 What about your brother and your sister, did it change it with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did you spend your Sundays any differently now that you were working in a full time job?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Oh no, I went to Church and Sunday School just the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 
You told me earlier something of how you spent your spare time, swimming and going to athletics and that sort of thing, did you continue to spend your spare time in the same way now that you were working or did you do different things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 I spent it in just the same way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Going to swimming and athletics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Nothing else at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Well night school. And night school at our Church, they had the girls' club, you kno
w, embroidery class and different things. And they had socials.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did you go out in the evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Where did you go to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Only to our Church and to night school, I never went gadding about.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Who did you go with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 My girl friends, that lived round about. My finance was at the war you see, we were engaged.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did you make any new friends - boys or girls - at this time? While you were at work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes, but not from work. At our Church there was always new members joining and 
it was our duty to make them welcome, and therefore we made new friends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 And you met them mostly at the Albert Hall?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes. We'd say are you coming to such a thing on such a night and then they'd come, you see. Otherwise if nobody had took any not
ice they wouldn't have come.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did you ever bring friends home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Oh yes. But my mother didn't welcome them. But after she died I used to have friends come home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Why didn't she welcome them do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 I don't know. I think it was just 
jealousy. I was the middle one, and her love was for the middle one and her admiration for the older one.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did you have any special friends at this time? Boys or girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 A lot of friends at Church and in the Sunday class, you know, all one age in the Sunday class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 You told me before you had a special boy friend, though, Mr. Bart?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Where did you go with these friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Oh we didn't go anywhere, only to the Albert Hall, because there was something on every night. Saturday ni
ghts they had wonderful concerts in the large hall.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did your parents meet your friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Yes, occasionally, but me mother wouldn't let me take many home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did they except to know where you were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Oh yes, but they always knew 'cos they knew where I spent my spare time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 And did you have to be in by a certain time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 
Yes, I had to be in by ten o'clock. If it was five past, I got run. She told me what she thought. I didn't get a good hiding or anything, but she'd carry on terrible.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15025541 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Did you have any interest in politics, when you were young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16719801 NB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14157171\charrsid16389298 Well not in those days, not before 1918.
\par }}